HEADWORD: Bluffy
<hw>Bluff"y</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
bluffs, or bold, steep banks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inclined to be bluff; brusque.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

